# Frontend Package

React frontend using Vite, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, and shadcn/ui components.

## Architecture

```
src/
├── api/            # API client functions
├── components/     # React components
│   └── ui/         # shadcn/ui components (don't modify)
├── pages/          # Page components (route targets)
├── hooks/          # Custom React hooks
├── lib/            # Utility functions
└── App.tsx         # Main app with routing
```

## UI Components

**Always use shadcn/ui components from `src/components/ui/`.** Don't pull in new UI libraries or build custom components unless truly necessary.

Available components:
- Layout: card, separator, tabs, accordion, collapsible, resizable, scroll-area
- Forms: button, input, textarea, checkbox, radio-group, select, switch, slider, form, label
- Feedback: alert, alert-dialog, dialog, drawer, sheet, popover, hover-card, tooltip, sonner (toast)
- Navigation: breadcrumb, dropdown-menu, menubar, navigation-menu, pagination, context-menu
- Display: avatar, badge, skeleton, table, progress, carousel, chart, aspect-ratio
- Command: command (cmdk), input-otp

**For toasts, use `sonner`:**

```typescript
import { toast } from "sonner";

toast.success("Operation completed");
toast.error("Something went wrong");
```

## API Client Patterns

API functions go in `src/api/`. They handle HTTP requests and type the responses:

```typescript
import axios from "axios";

const API_URL = import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL;

export interface MyItem {
  id: number;
  name: string;
  createdAt: string;
  updatedAt: string;
}

export const getMyItems = async (token: string): Promise<MyItem[]> => {
  const response = await axios.get<{ success: boolean; data: MyItem[] }>(
    `${API_URL}/api/my-items`,
    {
      headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` },
    }
  );
  return response.data.data;
};

export const createMyItem = async (
  token: string,
  data: { name: string }
): Promise<MyItem> => {
  const response = await axios.post<{ success: boolean; data: MyItem }>(
    `${API_URL}/api/my-items`,
    data,
    {
      headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` },
    }
  );
  return response.data.data;
};
```

Export from `src/api/index.ts`:

```typescript
export * from "./myItems";
```

## Page Component Patterns

```typescript
import { useEffect, useState } from "react";
import { useAuth } from "react-oidc-context";
import { toast } from "sonner";

import * as api from "../api";
import { MyItem } from "../api/myItems";
import { Button } from "../components/ui/button";
import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from "../components/ui/card";

export default function MyItemsPage() {
  const auth = useAuth();
  const [items, setItems] = useState<MyItem[]>([]);
  const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(true);

  useEffect(() => {
    const fetchItems = async () => {
      if (!auth.user?.access_token) return;
      
      try {
        const data = await api.getMyItems(auth.user.access_token);
        setItems(data);
      } catch (error: any) {
        console.error("Error fetching items:", error);
        toast.error(error.response?.data?.message || "Failed to fetch items");
      } finally {
        setIsLoading(false);
      }
    };

    fetchItems();
  }, [auth.user?.access_token]);

  if (isLoading) {
    return <div>Loading...</div>;
  }

  return (
    <div className="container mx-auto p-4">
      <h1 className="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">My Items</h1>
      {/* Content */}
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Routing

Routes are defined in `src/App.tsx` using React Router:

```typescript
import { lazy } from "react";
import { Route, Routes } from "react-router-dom";

const MyPage = lazy(() => import("./pages/MyPage"));

// In the Routes component:
<Route path="/my-page" element={<MyPage />} />
```

## Authentication

Use `react-oidc-context` for auth:

```typescript
import { useAuth } from "react-oidc-context";

const auth = useAuth();

// Check if authenticated
if (!auth.isAuthenticated) { /* redirect */ }

// Get access token for API calls
const token = auth.user?.access_token;

// Get user info
const email = auth.user?.profile.email;
```

## Styling

- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Use the `cn()` utility from `src/lib/utils` for conditional classes:

```typescript
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";

<div className={cn("base-class", isActive && "active-class")} />
```

## Testing

Tests use Vitest with React Testing Library:

```typescript
import { render, screen } from "@testing-library/react";
import { describe, expect, it } from "vitest";
import { Button } from "./button";

describe("Button", () => {
  it("renders with text", () => {
    render(<Button>Click me</Button>);
    expect(screen.getByRole("button", { name: "Click me" })).toBeInTheDocument();
  });
});
```

Run tests: `yarn workspace @harbor-app/frontend test`
